\section{Conclusions}
\begin{itemize}
\item EVs can be isolated and analyzed from biofluids (liquid biospy)
\item EVs are involved in tumor related processes
\item EVs carry information about their cell of origin and function
\item EVs populations in blood are heterogeneous. This is the major issue with their analysis
\item Deconvolution approaches are possible but not yet well established
\item The analysis of EVs together with other molecules in liquid biopsies (cfDNA) can be more informative in respect to the analysis of a single analyte alone. Multi-analyte approach 
\end{itemize}














